From: Baraka Malila <bmalila87@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 15:37:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?Remove=20data/99-nvidia-ac.rules=20=E2=80=94=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?crash=20trigger=20on=20FA507NV?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Upstream ships this udev rule OPTIONAL (never installed by Makefile,
noted as such in CHANGELOG). It starts/stops nvidia-powerd.service on
AC power state changes, which on ASUS FA507NV exercises the
nv_acpi_powersource_hotplug_event codepath that can deadlock the NVIDIA
driver under GPU load — full system LOCKUP.

Removing the file from the source tree prevents any downstream packager
(us and others) from accidentally sweeping it into a .deb via
data/*.rules glob. Belt-and-suspenders defense against a documented
crash trigger.

Motivation, prior symptoms, and detection are documented in
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-02-nvidia-ac-rule-decision.md in the
Ubuntu packaging tree.
---
 data/99-nvidia-ac.rules | 4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)
 delete mode 100644 data/99-nvidia-ac.rules

diff --git a/data/99-nvidia-ac.rules b/data/99-nvidia-ac.rules
deleted file mode 100644
index aecd212..0000000
--- a/data/99-nvidia-ac.rules
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,4 +0,0 @@
-# Stop nvidia_powerd on battery
-SUBSYSTEM=="power_supply",ENV{POWER_SUPPLY_ONLINE}=="0",RUN+="/usr/bin/systemctl --no-block stop nvidia-powerd.service"
-# Start nvidia_powerd on AC
-SUBSYSTEM=="power_supply",ENV{POWER_SUPPLY_ONLINE}=="1",RUN+="/usr/bin/systemctl --no-block start nvidia-powerd.service"
-- 
